      ec1118:'Bone-dry, fast and bulletproof, but strips delicate aromatics — use only if you want a crisp, sparkling-base traditional rather than an aromatic one.',
      '71b':'Rounds the honey slightly and softens any acidity; pleasant but a touch of its own ester character competes with a pure show mead.',
      qa23:'Adds a crisp, faintly citrus/tropical lift — nice on pale floral honeys, drink young.',
      us05:'Ale yeast — leaves a malty-clean blandness and caps around 11% ABV. Wrong tool for a honey showcase.',
      w15:'Stops sweet by design — turns a show mead syrupy and muddies the honey clarity you want here.'
